Acceptance Criteria:
Given a valid form with Full Name, Parent Name, Parent Email, Parent Phone;
When Admin clicks Save;
Then a new Student and Parent record is created, Activity_Log is written, and the UI navigates to the Student detail view.
And if mandatory fields are missing or email is invalid, the system shows an inline error.

Given an existing Active student;
When Admin edits fields and clicks Save; Then the profile is updated and Activity_Log records the mutation.
When Admin clicks Deactivate; Then the student status becomes Inactive.

Given a student with an active package;
When Admin inputs Amount (VND), Payment Method (Cash/Bank Transfer), Payment Date and clicks Save;
Then a Payment record is created, Remaining_Sessions is recalculated, and MSG-03 success toast appears.

Given active Teachers and Rooms exist;
When Admin fills in the Create Session form and saves;
Then if no conflicts: Session is saved and immediately visible to the assigned Teacher.
If conflict: system triggers UC-05 conflict flow and shows MSG-01.

Given a 409 conflict response;
When Admin views the Conflict Alert Screen and selects an alternative Room or Teacher;
And clicks Save;
Then system validates again and if clear: Session is saved successfully.

Given the System Timer has generated renewal alerts;
When Admin opens the Renewal Alerts List;
Then all flagged students (remaining sessions ≤ threshold) are listed with Parent Phone.
When Admin marks an alert as Resolved; Then its status changes to Resolved.

Given a Teacher is logged in;
When the Teacher opens My Timetable;
Then sessions assigned to that Teacher_ID are displayed chronologically.
And Teacher can switch between Daily and Weekly views.
And clicking a session card shows Class Session Details.

Given a completed session;
When Teacher opens Attendance tab and marks all students (Present/Absent/Late) and clicks Submit;
Then Attendance records are saved (deducting 1 session per BR-04).
And system triggers Email Gateway dispatch (UC-11) to notify parents.

Given a completed session within SLA window;
When Teacher enters Score (1–10) and Feedback Context and clicks Submit;
Then Feedback is saved against the Session and Student.
If SLA breached (> 12 hours): submission flagged as Late and violation logged (MSG-02).

Given the cron job triggers at 00:00;
When scanning active student_packages;
Then for each package with remaining_sessions ≤ threshold: if no existing Pending alert exists, insert a new alert_notification (type=Renewal).
And the job completes scanning 5,000 records within < 3 minutes (NFR-Performance).

Given a payload exists in the notification queue;
When the Email Gateway picks it up;
Then an HTML email is dispatched over SMTP/API (256-bit encryption).
And alert_notification status is updated to Sent.
If SMTP fails: system retries up to 3 times exponentially before logging failure.

Given valid credentials (email + password);
When POST /api/v1/auth/login is called;
Then 200 response with JWT access token and user info (role, fullName, email).
Given any API called without a valid JWT;
Then 401 Unauthorized returned.
Given user clicks Logout;
Then token is invalidated and user redirected to Login screen.

Given Admin is authenticated;
When Admin creates a Teacher with Full Name, Email, Password;
Then Teacher account is created with role=teacher.
When Admin deactivates a Teacher; Then teacher can no longer log in.
